ARGUMENT

| Step | Hyp | Ref | Expression |
|---|---|---|---|

| 1 |  | hbn.1 | |- ( ph -> A. x ph ) |
| 2 |  | #P_id | |- ( ph -> ph ) |
| 3 | 1, 2 | #P_exlimih | |- ( E. x ph -> ph ) |
| 4 | 3 | #P_con3i | |- ( -. ph -> -. E. x ph ) |
| 5 |  | #P_alnex | |- ( A. x -. ph <-> -. E. x ph ) |
| 6 | 4, 5 | #P_sylibr | |- ( -. ph -> A. x -. ph ) |
\
 If ` x ` is not free in ` ph ` , it is not free in ` -. ph ` .  This theorem doesn't use ~ ax6b compared to ~ hbnt .  (Contributed by GD, 27-Jan-2018.)
